_:N20501afc447d449abc2e3e4bb5858365 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Phil Douglas is the Director General of Border Force at the Home Office. He is also the statutory Director of Border Revenue, reporting to ministers at HM Treasury.</p>\n\n<p>Phil has held a variety of senior roles across the Home Office, including in national security, Border Force (where he was Regional Director for Heathrow Airport), enforcement and asylum policy.</p>\n\n<p>Outside the Home Office, he has also worked at the Ministry of Justice, the European Commission, and at the former UK Representation to the European Union.</p>\n\n<p>Phil started his civil service career as an immigration officer at Heathrow Airport.</p>\n\n<p>Phil was appointed a Companion of the Order of the Bath in the 2025 Birthday Honours for services to border security and public service.</p>\n" .
